cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 150 mi WNW of Havana, Cuba
cyclone.trajectory: crossing the southeastern Gulf of Mexico and then turning north toward the northern Gulf Coast (Florida Panhandle/Alabama) Monday night, before moving inland toward Tennessee by mid-week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: northern Gulf Coast, most likely the Florida Panhandle or Alabama coast

weather_observation.impacted_coast: Coastline from Mississippi eastward to the Florida Panhandle and Big Bend region
weather_observation.wind: Only breezy conditions expected as remnants pass well south; sustained tropical-storm-force winds not anticipated
weather_observation.rainfall: Light to moderate rain (generally <2 inches) possible late week as remnants move northeast of the Ohio Valley
weather_observation.other_hazards: Minor localized flooding possible in low-lying or poor-drainage areas if pockets of heavier rain reach Lake Erie basin
